---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Now — Sambulo Senda" description="A snapshot of what I'm focused on right now.">
  <div class="page">
    <div class="page-head">
      <h1 class="page-title">Now</h1>
      <span class="page-meta">UPDATED JUN 2026</span>
    </div>

    <p class="now-intro">A snapshot of what's got my attention right now.</p>

    <div class="now-grid">
      <div class="now-k">WORKING ON</div>
      <p class="now-v">
        <em>Versify Bible</em> and <em>Scribe Scan</em> &mdash; both live on the App Store. Most of
        my writing energy goes into React Native's New Architecture: Fabric, TurboModules, and the
        migration work that comes with them.
      </p>

      <div class="now-k">READING</div>
      <p class="now-v">Tony Fadell's <em>Build</em>, on the train. Slow and good.</p>

      <div class="now-k">TINKERING</div>
      <p class="now-v">
        On-device LLM inference on iPhone &mdash; seeing how far you can get without ever touching a
        server.
      </p>

      <div class="now-k">BASED IN</div>
      <p class="now-v">
        London. Open to consulting from Q3 2026 &mdash; <a class="clink" href="/contact">say hello</a>.
      </p>
    </div>

    <p class="now-note">
      This is a <a class="clink" href="https://nownownow.com/about" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">now page</a>.
      If you want to chat about any of this, <a class="clink" href="https://cal.com/sambulosenda" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">book a call</a>
      or <a class="clink" href="mailto:sambulosendas@gmail.com">email me</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</Layout>
